	</p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">2026 </span><span class="csC2FEE544">REGULAR SESSION</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">Introduced</span></p><p class="cs3E63B65"><span class="cs8498B7A6">House Bill 4727</span></p><p class="csFF933113"><span class="csADC6E5DB">By Delegates Pritt, Brooks, Stephens, Foggin, Shamblin, Jordan, Toney, Dittman, Bell, Ferrell, and Bridges</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Introduced January 22, 2026; referred to the Committee on Education then Finance]</span></p><p class="cs29F66C3F"><span class="csEF05ACC">A BILL to amend and reenact &sect;18A-4-2 of the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, relating to providing a 25% pay increase for state teachers across all salary scales.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
